<br>
2. You must carry large ammounts of money around, even if you are pick pocketed, you will always get all of your money back.<br>
<br>
3. When seeking the Great sword, you must first cross the plains of dispair, but in order to do that, you must get an air ship. The guy who owns the air ship doesn't lend it out. He does however collect rare animal cards.  There is a shop that sells rare animal cards, however they are expensive, you might make a trade with the woman that owns it if you can find a special herb that grows in the cave near her town.<br>
<br>
4. Repeating fragments of town peoples sentences can indeed get them to give you quests.<br>
<br>
5. The main boss always unestimates you even though you have traveled to the center of the planet and killed all of his friends.<br>
<br>
6. The female lead always is a healer and becomes to love the male lead. <br>
<br>
7. It is possable to carry many items around, no matter the size, and they characters whom are entrusted with the items always know where they are.<br>
<br>
8. Guns shoot rubber bullets, unless you're the main character using a gun.<br>
<br>
9. Food = HP!!!<br>
<br>
10.  The kid with the blue hair will cause trouble!! Avoid him! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugenocommand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GenoCommand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/26/02 10:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   games</span><hr size=1> running over 12 people=1 wanted star<br>
