<br>
-To be a Jedi, you need to have a beard, wear pyjamas, be an alien, or all of the above. Unless you're Luke Skywalker.<br>
<br>
-Gold armour is better than steel armour. Likewise, a bandana will protect more efficiently against sword blows than a helmet.<br>
<br>
-When you get more skilled at swordfighting you do more damage, despite the fact that you're still doing exactly the same thing with the sword that you were when you first picked it up.<br>
<br>
-You can run all the time, without getting tired. Just gotta find Caps Lock...<br>
<br>
-You can run just as fast backwards as forwards.<br>
<br>
-All guns must be held up to the face before you fire it, including rocket launchers. It's just more accurate.<br>
<br>
-Centre of gravity? What's that? It's a LIEEE!!!<br>
<br>
-Your minigun takes the same ammo as your pistol.<br>
<br>
-It's impossible to drop or fumble ammo while reloading your double-barrelled boomstick, 'cos you're skilled enough to reload the whole thing in 1.73 seconds, every time, while running off a ledge, dodging fireballs and hot-footing across lava.<br>
<br>
-Anything of use glows in the dark, including your car keys.<br>
<br>
-If your wife and child get brutally murdered, your expression will be of mild constipation.<br>
<br>
-If spotted in a top secret installation, you will be alerted to the danger by someone shouting &quot;Hey! You there!&quot;<br>
<br>
-If you ever fight Luke Skywalker, he'll wave his lightsaber randomly at you, run around for a bit, and fall down a hole, and accuse you of cheating.<br>
<br>
-I can get shot repeatedly with a chaingun, and still run around afterwards. 'cos my skin's made of LEAD, baby. <p><div align="center">
